  "title": "ISic002131. I.Sicily inscription 002131",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  <a id=\"aa-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.</span>ΟΝΦ̣[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"aa-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΑΥΡ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">fragment (physical) b</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--interpretive\">  <a id=\"ab-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"ab-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abc\">fragment (physical) c</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divc--interpretive\">  <a id=\"ac-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΔΕ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"ac-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.</span>ΤΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--diplomatic\"><a id=\"aa-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span>ΟΝ.[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"aa-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΑΥΡ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">fragment (physical) b</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--diplomatic\"><a id=\"ab-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"ab-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abc\">fragment (physical) c</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divc--diplomatic\"><a id=\"ac-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]ΙΔΕ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"ac-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·</span>ΤΑ[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text based upon drawings in Agnello 1956</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The largest fragment (a) was published by Orsi in 1923, without reference to the existence of a Greek text on the reverse. The other two fragments were published, together with the first fragment, by Agnello in 1956, but he only provided drawings of each, stating that the fragments did not join and declined to attempt any editing of the text. The fragments appear to offer a typical example of the re-use of an imperial period Latin funerary plaque for a later Greek funerary plaque in the catacombs.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Orsi 1923 no.4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001699\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001699</a>  </li><li> Agnello 1956 26 p, fig.7a-c <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002207\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002207</a>  </li><li> Marchese 2012 no.43 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002550\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002550</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
